arStrings.szText: Campaña - Hawe - Templo - Los jugadores encuentran el dedo de Elias
Well, well. Elias’ finger. He bound his life essence to a piece of himself. Clever.
To self. Admiring the spellcraft. As a necromancer, the Player thinks what Elias has done--binding his soul to a finger--is smart. Think of it as a horcrux.
Ach. This...this is Elias’ finger. He hid a piece of himself here to stay immortal.
To self. Disgusted. Puzzling out the mystery and connecting the dots--Elias kept his finger safe and sound here, which is the key to his immortality. Think of the finger as a horcrux.
